Victory College Ikare, Ondo State, will hold a seven-day commemoration of its 75th Founders’ Day between February 21 and 27, 2022. A statement by the National President of Old Students’ Association (VICOSA) of Victory College Ikare, Prof. Michael Faborode, and the Chairman of the Anniversary Planning and Implementation Committee, Otunba Olusoga Orogun, promised a successful event.   ‘How to curb brain drain in health sector’     Alleged assault, misconduct: Senate President, AGF ask CCT…     Cocoa factory plans $1m pilot export to boost foreign…   The committee has Olugbenga Ajanaku (Co-Chairman), Yinka Jonah (Secretary), Olufemi Oyewole (Member) and Adedoyin Alao (Member). An anniversary service will hold on February 21, while a thanksgiving service will take place on February 27, 2022. Students of Victory College, Ikare, and other colleges are expected to participate in an inter-school quiz competition on February 22 as well as an inter-house sport on February 23. SPONSORED